{{NCAATeamFootballSeason |Year=2008 |Team=Missouri Tigers |Image= |Conference=Big 12 Conference |Division=North |ShortConference=Big 12 |CoachRank=16 |APRank=19 |BCSRank=<!-- No final BCS Poll --> |Record= 10â4 |ConfRecord=5â3 |HeadCoach=[[Gary Pinkel]] |OffCoach=[[Dave Christensen]] |DefCoach=[[Matt Eberflus]] |OScheme=[[Spread offense|Spread]] |DScheme=[[4â3 defense|4â3]] |StadiumArena=[[Faurot Field]] (c. 68,349) |Champion=Big 12 North Co-Champions |BowlTourney=[[2008 Alamo Bowl|Alamo Bowl]] vs. [[2008 Northwestern Wildcats football team|Northwestern]] |BowlTourneyResult= W 30â23 (OT) |ConfChamp = [[2008 Big 12 Championship Game|Big 12 Championship]] vs. [[2008 Oklahoma Sooners football team|Oklahoma]] |ConfChampResult = L 21â62 }} {{2008 Big 12 football standings}} The '''2008 [[Missouri Tigers]] [[Missouri Tigers football|football team]]''' represented the [[University of Missouri]] in [[college football|college football's]] [[2008 NCAA Division I FBS football season|2008 season]]. The team was coached by [[Gary Pinkel]], who returned in his eighth season with Mizzou, and played their home games at [[Faurot Field|Faurot Field at Memorial Stadium]].
Quarterback [[Chase Daniel]] returned for his final year of eligibility and led the Tigers to a second appearance in the [[Big 12 Football Championship Game|Big 12 Championship Game]].<ref name="Five Tigers">Associated Press. [http://www.newschannel10.com/global/story.asp?s=7596730 Five Tigers to stay next year, drop NFL Draft plan] January 8, 2008 {{dead link|date=September 2011}}</ref>
==Recruits== '''Key Losses''': * SS Cornelius "Pig" Brown * WR [[William Franklin (American football)|William Franklin]]<ref name="Good news for MU"/> * OT Tyler Luellen<ref name="Good news for MU"/> * TE [[Martin Rucker (American football)|Martin Rucker]]<ref name="Good news for MU">Watson, Graham. [http://www.stltoday.com/stltoday/sports/stories.nsf/mizzou/story/8D7D38081FFA6E8F862573C50017B791?OpenDocument Good news for MU is that 2008 could be even better] ''St. Louis Post-Dispatch'', January 3, 2008. {{dead link|date=September 2011}}</ref> * C Adam Spieker<ref name="Good news for MU"/> * RB [[Tony Temple]]<ref name="Good news for MU"/>
Five junior Tigers will return for the 2008 season after turning down the NFL Draft, including QB [[Chase Daniel]], TE Chase Coffman, SS William Moore, DE Stryker Sulak and DT Ziggy Hood.<ref name="Five Tigers"/> The Tigers will have 16 returning starters, 10 on defense and six on offense.<ref name="draft-worthy">DeArmond, Mike. [http://www.kansascity.com/sports/story/436735.html Missouri's five draft-worthy juniors all returning] ''Kansas City Star'', January 8, 2008. {{dead link|date=September 2011}}</ref>
[[Redshirt (college sports)|Redshirt]] freshman DE John Stull was removed from the team on January 11, 2008, after being arrested on drug charges.<ref name="MU's Stull is kicked off team">Watson, Graham. [http://www.stltoday.com/stltoday/sports/stories.nsf/mizzou/story/9F0F9D07A2BB4BAD862573CE0015E012?OpenDocument MU's Stull is kicked off team] ''St. Louis Post-Dispatch'', January 12, 2008 {{dead link|date=September 2011}}</ref>
