 = Missouri 2008 Football Commitments | scout ref title = 2008 Missouri Commits | espn ref title = 2008 Player Commitments - Missouri | scout overall = 31 | rivals overall = 25 | espn overall = | rivals school = 22 | scout s = 19 | espn schoolid = 142 | accessdate = 2008-08-01 | bball = | collapse = no }}
Following their [[2008 Cotton Bowl Classic|Cotton Bowl Classic]] victory, Mizzou landed a number of previously committed recruits from the state of Missouri. QB Blaine Gabbert from Ballwin, MO is the No. 1 rated prep player in the state of Missouri, and No. 1 rated pro-style quarterback in his recruiting class.<ref>[http://www.stltoday.com/stltoday/sports/stories.nsf/mizzou/story/C73F6BE3667D59C4862573E700180713?OpenDocument ''St. Louis Post-Dispatch:'' Gabbert is Mizzou's star attraction] {{dead link|date=September 2011}}</ref> and the Tigers landed him after he had previously committed to [[Nebraska Cornhuskers football|Nebraska]].<ref name="St. Louis receiver">DeArmond, Mike. [http://www.kansascity.com/news/breaking_news/story/434681.html St. Louis receiver switches to Mizzou] ''Kansas City Star'', January 7, 2008. {{dead link|date=September 2011}}</ref> According to [http://www.rivals.com Rivals] rankings, the Tigers also landed WR Wes Kemp (#5), TE Andrew Jones (#3), DE Alden Smith (#6) and RB Drew Temple (#11), brother of former Tigers player [[Tony Temple]] all from in-state high schools.<ref name="Missouri Commit List for 2008">[http://missouri.rivals.com/commitlist.asp Missouri Commitments List 2008] ''Rivals.com''. Retrieved January 8, 2008.</ref>
From out of state, the Tigers landed OT Dan Hoch, who like Gabbert previously committed to Nebraska.<ref name="Iowa HS">DeArmond, Mike. [http://www.kansascity.com/167/story/435658.html Iowa HS football star who committed to Huskers changes to Missouri] ''Kansas City Star'', January 8, 2008. {{dead link|date=September 2011}}</ref>
